    },
    {
      "id": "quote:ad35e04581fb838f",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 511,
        "char_start": 409,
        "episode_id": "1c0614c2-9f65-5fd5-9340-ab8c6059d014",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-01",
        "text": "What does the failure mode look like? What's the structural angle most listeners don't have access to?",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 24000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 18000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p08_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
      "id": "quote:f103a987b4483dcd",
      "properties": {
        "char_end": 713,
        "char_start": 533,
        "episode_id": "1c0614c2-9f65-5fd5-9340-ab8c6059d014",
        "speaker_id": "person:speaker-02",
        "text": "Yeah, so — A newsroom is a reliability system with a deadline. We've seen this play out at teams using BBC. The framing matters because it tells you which trade-offs you're making.",
        "timestamp_end_ms": 30000,
        "timestamp_start_ms": 24000,
        "transcript_ref": "transcripts/p08_e03.txt"
      },
      "type": "Quote"
    },
    {
